{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a6f65546-53cb-460b-8984-9148e9bb961f","content":"Here's what to do:\n\n1. **Remove** the `xunit.runner.visualstudio` package reference.\n\n2. **Add** the `xunit.v3.runner.mtp` package (xUnit v3) **or** if staying on xUnit v2, add `xunit.runner.mtp` instead:\n\n   ```xml\n   <!-- For xUnit v2 (your current version): -->\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.mtp\" Version=\"1.*\" />\n\n   <!-- OR migrate to xUnit v3: -->\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.v3\" Version=\"1.*\" />\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.v3.runner.mtp\" Version=\"1.*\" />\n   ```\n\n3. **Enable MTP** in your project file:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TestingPlatformDotNetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotNetTestSupport>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n4. **Run tests** with:\n   ```bash\n   dotnet test\n   ```\n   Or run the test executable directly (MTP produces a standalone executable).\n\n**Key notes:**\n- `TestingPlatformDotNetTestSupport` ensures `dotnet test` uses MTP instead of VSTest.\n- If you're open to upgrading to **xUnit v3**, that's the recommended path — it has native MTP support and is actively developed. However, v3 has API changes (e.g., `Xunit` → `Xunit.v3` namespace changes, `Assert` updates).\n- If you want to stay on **xUnit v2.9.3**, use `xunit.runner.mtp` as a bridge.\n\nWould you like help modifying a specific `.csproj` file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"f417a024-df22-4ac3-a6e0-b73f82efc437","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to migrate their xUnit.net project from VSTest (using xunit.runner.visualstudio) to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP). Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":490,"requestId":"0434:1CDF9E:1E72373:2240DEC:69E819EC"},"id":"53876ebe-f0ac-4f6d-b0b7-25d013c10fd7","timestamp":"2026-04-22T00:44:38.981Z","parentId":"fe2ad2f0-41ee-49e9-a74b-cc6fe6f86841"}
